That'll be a problem as soon as either your OS and home directories or
your media library grow beyond the artificially small space you've given
them. While I'm not generally a fan of the &quot;space is cheap&quot; mantra, this
is one of the scenarios where I think it's a good answer.

Get a 500GB FireWire drive and dedicate the internal drive to non-media
files. Or even better, ignore the internal drive completely. One of the
easiest (as compared to cheapest) performance upgrades for a mini is to
boot from an external FW drive. You have more performance, more space
and less heat.
