If is an Intel Mini, get a male/female Sata plug or a male to female
Sata cable and connect a full size 7200 rpm 300+gb Sata2 drive (about
$50-60 used now) for lots of storage space and sell of that toy hard
drive.  Your Mini will run cooler without that heat generator in there.
While you're at it, toss the slot loading optical drive and replace it
at 1/3 the price you can sell the optical drive for (you'll need a
USB/firewire external drive for that as well but that should only be
$10-15 used for USB or a little more for firewire.  The slot loading
drives tend to die a lot faster than the full size ones.  And make sure
you have a backup system that works.  And you use it.  Then you'll be
set.  OS X goes into meltdown so rarely, partitioning is almost never
used any more.  This ain't Windows baby.
</POST>
